  "title": "ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>1. To assist Project Manager</p><p>2. To support the site construction team in ensuring smooth execution of work</p><p>3. To plan ahead of schedule so that site problems can be resolved before they have an impact on cost, overall schedule, and quality</p><p>4. Day-to-day management of the site, including supervising and monitoring the site labor force and the work of any sub-contractor</p><p>5. Liaising with local authorities, clients, sub-contractors, and consultants to resolve any commercial and contractual matter</p><p>6. Checking and ensuring all plans and work are as per specifications</p><p>7. Resolving any technical problems/difficulties that may arise on site</p><p>8. To ensure proper handover of the project to the client</p><p><em><strong>Job Requirement</strong></em></p><p>• Degree in Civil Engineering</p><p>• At least 2 years of relevant working experience</p>",
